name: The Fool
description: A step into the void, heart open to possibility: the beginning of everything, where consciousness has yet to know itself.

name: The Magician
description: The spark of will manifests: what you imagine can be created.

name: The High Priestess
description: Silence guards the soul’s secrets: there is power in knowledge and in the need to wait.

name: The Empress
description: Life grows where there is room to feel: abundance is nourished by beauty, care, and fertile vision.

name: The Emperor
description: Seeking order to shape chaos: a structure is born to contain creative fire.

name: The Hierophant
description: Listen to the voice that unites spirit and body. Welcome its guidance with discernment.

name: The Lovers
description: To love is a political act: meeting the other reveals parts of oneself, and love demands courage.

name: The Chariot
description: Willpower finds its direction: to move forward is an act of identity affirmation.

name: Justice
description: Everything finds its balance, sooner or later: truth will emerge between the world’s invisible lines.

name: The Hermit
description: Those who seek the light often find it in the darkness of introspection: the inner path is unhurried, but it leads far.

name: The Wheel of Fortune
description: Nothing stands still, yet every cycle has meaning: fate turns, and the soul learns by dancing with the new.

name: Strength
description: Tenderness is more powerful than it seems. Those who embrace their identity become myth.

name: The Hanged Man
description: To reverse perspective is to die a little: sometimes it’s by stopping that we go further.

name: Death
description: What ends creates space: not all that dies is a loss—some things set us free.

name: Temperance
description: Every excess seeks its center: art lies in mixing, and to flow is to live.

name: The Devil
description: What do you truly crave when no one is watching? Chains are light as feathers, but who holds them?

name: The Tower
description: The fall is a blessing: among the rubble, you finally breathe.

name: The Star
description: After destruction, a whisper of hope: beauty is naked, it shines, and asks no permission.

name: The Moon
description: Not everything that shines is immediately clear: the unconscious, dreams, and fear naturally accompany revelation.

name: The Sun
description: Joy that radiates without reason: your truth, when shared, becomes light for others.

name: Judgement
description: The inner voice that calls us to remember who we are: the final awakening, and it happens when we are ready.

name: The World
description: All that needed to happen has happened: the soul, the circle closes—but only to dance again.
